<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5679> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5679" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Domitius Calvinus to Cilicia to summon reinforcements against the invasion of Pharnaces of Pontus (Bell. Alex. 34.5). Münzer (RE) suggests that the name Patisius is an error for Patiscus (cf. Cic. Fam. 2.11.2; 8.9.3; and the Index, on Patiscus)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10466> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10466" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. Caes. 67.4-5, App. BC 2.119. Joined the Liberators on the Capitol on the Ides of March. Unlike C. Octavius and Lentulus Spinther, he is not explicitly mentioned as having claimed to have been an assassin, but might have been a senator nonetheless." .
